 <br><br>On the circulation front, the Galway Races delivered a great sales  return across both the Mirror (8.5% week-on-week increase) and the Star (12% week-on-week increase) despite having no free bets this year, which we had last year. The Irish Daily Star also had a free Premier League fixtures magazine on the Friday of Galway week...The cover price increases across the whole Reach Ireland portfolio coincided with return of the Premier League on Saturday 12th August, and early market indications are suggesting that all titles are holding up well and ahead of budget for the month, which is encouraging.
